{{Quote|I am QT-3PO, protocol droid. I have been asked to relate what I know of those disgusting creatures: the Jawas.|QT-3PO|<ref name="Life" />}}
'''QT-3PO''' was a [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]]. Shortly before the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], QT-3PO and its [[QT-3PO's master|master]] set down in [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] in their [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]]. While the freighter was being repaired, QT-3PO wandered off to explore, but was forcibly abducted by the [[Jawa/Legends|Jawas]]<ref name="Life" /> of [[Nebit/Legends|Nebit's]] [[Nebit's tribe/Legends|clan]]<ref name="VG">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iv/explore/visualguides/chp08.html|text=Visual Guide — Chapter 8: Droids for Sale}}</ref> at [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]]-point.<ref name="Life" /> There, QT-3PO observed Jawa society and the interior of their [[Sandcrawler/Legends|sandcrawler]].<ref name="Life" />

The sandcrawler later recovered two other [[Droid/Legends|droids]] in the desert&mdash;[[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]].<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref> By this point, QT-3PO had been extensively damaged<ref name="Visual Guide Chapter 7">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iv/explore/visualguides/chp07.html|text=Episode IV Visual Guide &mdash; Chapter 7: Land of the Jawas}}</ref>, but was still able to relate the story of his time on the sandcrawler to C-3PO.<ref name="VG" /> Shortly after C-3PO and R2-D2 were sold to the [[Lars family/Legends|Lars family]],<ref name="ANH" /> QT-3PO was discovered and purchased back by their master, who paid the Jawa's asking price. QT-3PO later reported on his experience with the Jawas.<ref name="Life" />

